This is Debian GNU/Linux's prepackaged version of the 'xlock' utility.
'xlock' locks the X server until the user enters his/her password at the 
keyboard. 'xlock' was originally written by Patrick J. Naughton, the 
'xlockmore' extended version is written and maintained by David A. Bagley.
Various modes have been contributed by other programmers.

The current debian package maintainer is Michael Stone <mstone@debian.org> and
is based on the version of xlockmore available at
ftp://ftp.tux.org/pub/people/david-bagley/xlockmore/xlockmore-5.31.tar.bz2
This debian package was originally compiled by Dirk Eddelbuettel
<edd@debian.org> and later maintained by Herbert Xu <herbert@debian.org>.

